cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with modeling human attention in panoramic video, which involves computer vision (CV) and human-computer interaction (HCI) aspects. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.HC are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also uses deep reinforcement learning (DRL) to predict head movement (HM) positions, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI and cs.LG. Finally, the paper deals with multimedia (MM) data in the form of panoramic video sequences, which makes cs.MM a likely sub-category as well.
